The 14-year-old girl accused of assaulting, fellow pupil, the late Lufuno Mavhunga, is now facing assault and grievous bodily harm charges. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Limpopo school girl accused of assaulting, fellow pupil, the late Lufuno Mavhunga is now facing assault and grievous bodily harm charges. The National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) says the video of the incident depicts more than just common assault. READ: Limpopo teen accused of assault to appear in court The suspect appeared at the Thohoyandou Magistrate's Court on Tuesday. She is set to appear in court again on Thursday for a bail application. It's believed 15-year-old Mavhunga took her own life, after a video showing her being assaulted, went viral on social media